reviews.text: This was our first time here. The atmosphere was laid back. We had Jonnae P. for our server and she was so patient with us. We took a little longer than normal because everything sounded so good. We had alligator for the appetizer, and it was amazing. I had the Shrimp Gabrielle and my husband had the Steak and Shrimp. They both were delicious. They definitely do hold back on the shrimp! We even went back a few hours later and had dessert. Which was just as amazing as the dinner. Hush puppies I recommend! They aren‚Äôt on menu but they do have them!

A quick walk from the Expo Center in downtown Des Moines! Great atmosphere! Food was not as flavorful, but I have a Southern palate, meaning I need less char and bland taste and more seasoning and fresher taste plus sweet tea. Probably great food if you're drinking, but I was there for brunch with teens. Busy day, so it was a long wait.

The place was busy for a Wednesday evening. Street and lot parking was available. We were a large party of 16. Adalynn, our server did a terrific job of getting our orders correctly and splitting the bill 7 different ways with people sitting all mixed up. The food was served reasonably quick for such a large group. All the meals were delicious and the servings were huge. Quite a few take home boxes! If you like spicy foods and a Cajun menu this is the place to go. Don't like spicy,  there were still good options. A bit noisy for conversations but definitely recommend for a good time.

Spectacular!! Walking distance from the Iowa event center, we loved everything we ordered. Armadillo eggs- jalape√±o popper, wrapped in chicken, wrapped in bacon- the entire family loved them! Alligator bites, with a yummy dipping sauce was awesome too! There were both so good, they disappeared before I could even take a picture! The hush puppies were to die for. Shrimp PoBoy, pork belly burger and seafood jambalaya were all absolutely amazing. 10/10 would recommend!

From what I remember, it was a great time. Good, knowledgeable and patient staff. Lots of interactions going on. Good vibrations. Had good beer(when I was into that) and great food when we went. Given this was apparently back on 9/18/20. Better late than never, I supposeüíØ.

God blessü§éüôèüèΩ

Don't know her name but she has three 3's going down her left sideburn area of the face, just in case you want to avoid her too. Apart from that, best food in the Midwest!!

Also love their crawfish etouffee. Great location for any event downtown but also worth a special trip.
